<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-909-514  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 909 514.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Nov 20 1989 n342 p152(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Azerty's channel-information project.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shalvoy, Mary Lee.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Azerty Inc, a distributor of computer supplies, accessories andperipherals, has introduced two solutions that address the firm'sneed to supply its dealer channel with information on itself.andP;  Thefirst is a pilot issue of a video-based magazine, which wasintroduced at the 1989 Fall Comdex show.andP;  The second involves thepublishing of its price list on floppy disk for all of itsresellers.andP;  The video is seen as the best way for a variety ofinformation to be distributed, as it is concise, can be used fordemonstration purposes and can reach a broad base of people.andP;  Thepremier issue covers such topics as successful direct-marketingand mail techniques and how to hire and train salespeople.andP;  Theprice list is available in both 5.25-inch and 3.5-inch versionsfor IBM and compatible computers and contains price information onAzerty's top 900 product listings.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Azerty Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     MarketingVideo RecordingsMagazinesPriceFloppy DiskDistributorsSuppliesPeripheralsAdvertisingPromotion of ProductCustomer Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>